sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>mTLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>ServiceAccount token
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>Framework-specific ports
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet<br/>8081/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: Training Job Submission (PyTorchJob Example)
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: User credentials
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: API Server mTLS
        Webhook->>K8sAPI: Validate job spec<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Validation result
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission response (allow/deny)
        K8sAPI-->>User: Job created

        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch PyTorchJob resources<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: PyTorchJob event (ADDED)

        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods (N replicas)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service for pod discovery<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap with training config<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token

        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
        K8sAPI-->>User: Status: Running
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 220)
        Note over Pods: Flow 4: Distributed Training Communication
        Pods->>Pods: Master Pod starts (rank 0)<br/>Port 23456/TCP
        Pods->>Pods: Worker Pods connect to Master<br/>TCP plaintext (framework-specific)<br/>Auth: None
        Pods->>Pods: Gradient synchronization<br/>TCP/UDP plaintext<br/>No encryption
        Note over Pods: Training data exchanged using<br/>PyTorch DistributedDataParallel<br/>or similar framework primitives
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection
        Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Auth: None (ClusterIP)
        Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>controller_queue_depth<br/>reconciliation_errors<br/>active_jobs_total
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over Kubelet,Controller: Flow 3: Health Monitoring
        Kubelet->>Controller: GET /healthz<br/>HTTP/8081<br/>Auth: None
        Controller-->>Kubelet: HTTP 200 OK
        Kubelet->>Controller: GET /readyz<br/>HTTP/8081<br/>Auth: None
        Controller-->>Kubelet: HTTP 200 OK
    end

    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over User,K8sAPI: Job Completion Flow
        Pods-->>K8sAPI: Pod exits (Success/Failure)
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Pod status change event
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>Status: Succeeded/Failed
        K8sAPI-->>User: kubectl get pytorchjob<br/>Status: Succeeded
    end
